About this item

  • Switch between the game and reality seamlessly - G06 simultaneously connects to PC/PS and phones. Without pausing your game, answer or hang up with just a click, or mute by holding for 1 second.
  • Effortless Wireless Gameplay - Transition from tangled cables to smooth wireless gaming. Leveraging a 2.4GHz connection through its USB dongle, this headset ensures consistent gameplay for PCs and many consoles. Note: Some consoles may not support this wireless feature.
  • Bluetooth Ready - Experience quick, lag-free audio connectivity. Switch to Bluetooth mode with a simple 2-tap and enjoy your favorite media seamlessly. Keep in mind: Microphone functionality may vary in Bluetooth mode depending on the device.
  • Wired Connection Supported - For those preferring a wired setup, connect to various gaming devices using a standard 3.5mm cable. Some systems may require additional adapters (not included). Note: Microphone mute feature may vary in wired mode.
  • Extended Gameplay Hours - Stay in the game longer with up to 100 hours of battery life. When it's time to recharge, be back to full power in just 4 hours. Elevate your gaming sessions with a headset that's designed for endurance.

How to Connect Your Wireless Headset for the First Time?

1. Press and hold the power button on your headset for 5 seconds to enter pairing mode.

2. Insert the USB dongle into your device (PC, console, etc.).

3. Once the USB dongle is connected, your headset will automatically pair with your device.

Why cant I connect G06 to my Xbox console?

Xbox doesnt support 2.4GHz or Bluetooth connections for G06. Use the 3.5mm audio cable with your Xbox controller.

How do I use the call alert feature?

Connect the headset to the console with the 2.4Ghz dongle. Press the power button twice for Bluetooth mode, pair with your phone, then press twice again to revert to wireless. This connects the headset to both the console and phone for call alerts.

How do I switch modes?

The headset starts in 2.4Ghz wireless mode by default. You can switch between wireless and Bluetooth modes by pressing the power button twice.

Can I play while charging?

For electrical safety, the G06 cannot be used while charging.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    4 out of 5 stars
    Almost what I'm looking for but has some limitations if you're a power user, still a nice headset.
    They are comfortable, the mic isn't super amazing but isn't bad either. Actually it's better than a lot of bigger name brand wireless headsets I was watching reviews on recently, it definitely is better than my old HyperX Cloud Stinger Wireless headset. The Audio playback is decent as well, a little better than my Cloud Stinger Wireless, a little worse maybe then my Sades Luna USB headset, maybe. I think I was just used to that headset from using it for so long, it's pretty close though.The range on these is pretty good, try to avoid plugging the 2.4GHz adapter into USB 3.0 port & make sure you don't have any USB 3.0 devices plugged in right next to it, USB 3.0 causes 2.4GHz interference. at first I had it connected to a USB 3.0 hub with a USB 3.0 SSD connected right next to it. This would cause it to drop out before even leaving the room, but simply plugging in a 3ft USB 2.0 extension cable first made it where I could walk across the whole house & even in the driveway it was still working.There are a few issues though, when pressing the power button it makes a little buzz before powering on, not sure if that is just my unit or if that is just how this is, Update 10/14/2023: after using it more it stopped doing that when powering it on.A bigger issue is plugging in the USB-C cable to charge it, shuts it off & can't be powered on till the USB cable is unplugged, I basically want something I have always have wired & charged then just unplug when I need to move away from my desk. Update 10/14/2023: I contacted their support, there is no way to power them on while charging. At least the battery life seems pretty good, I know they claim 100 hours. I haven't tried to test that claim but I used it all day without powering it off & it never died.Connecting the 3.5mm cable shuts it off as well, so you can't have it connected over bluetooth or the wireless adapter while connected to a wired device. For example use it to talk on the phone or discord on a laptop while playing music on your desktop. seems the hardware should be able to do it, just the firmware running on it prevents it.Also if you connect it wired to the computer & hold down the power & mute it makes a USB connect sound, then disconnects, too bad it can't run wired over USB while charging.Update 10/14/2023, at first I was almost thinking about returning this & spending more on a headset from one of the well known brands, but after using these more. I actually am starting to like them more, so I updated my review from 3 to 4 stars & after watching more reviews on more expensive headsets, it seems none are perfect no matter how much you spend.If you don't care about using them while the USB cable is connected or care about using wireless at the same time as the 3.5mm, I say these are still worth getting, they sound better than some more expensive wireless models from bigger brands.

    V3Tech
    4.0 out of 5 stars Almost what I'm looking for but has some limitations if you're a power user, still a nice headset.
    Reviewed in the United States on October 12, 2023
    Color: OrangeVerified Purchase
    They are comfortable, the mic isn't super amazing but isn't bad either. Actually it's better than a lot of bigger name brand wireless headsets I was watching reviews on recently, it definitely is better than my old HyperX Cloud Stinger Wireless headset. The Audio playback is decent as well, a little better than my Cloud Stinger Wireless, a little worse maybe then my Sades Luna USB headset, maybe. I think I was just used to that headset from using it for so long, it's pretty close though.

    The range on these is pretty good, try to avoid plugging the 2.4GHz adapter into USB 3.0 port & make sure you don't have any USB 3.0 devices plugged in right next to it, USB 3.0 causes 2.4GHz interference. at first I had it connected to a USB 3.0 hub with a USB 3.0 SSD connected right next to it. This would cause it to drop out before even leaving the room, but simply plugging in a 3ft USB 2.0 extension cable first made it where I could walk across the whole house & even in the driveway it was still working.

    There are a few issues though, when pressing the power button it makes a little buzz before powering on, not sure if that is just my unit or if that is just how this is, Update 10/14/2023: after using it more it stopped doing that when powering it on.

    A bigger issue is plugging in the USB-C cable to charge it, shuts it off & can't be powered on till the USB cable is unplugged, I basically want something I have always have wired & charged then just unplug when I need to move away from my desk. Update 10/14/2023: I contacted their support, there is no way to power them on while charging. At least the battery life seems pretty good, I know they claim 100 hours. I haven't tried to test that claim but I used it all day without powering it off & it never died.

    Connecting the 3.5mm cable shuts it off as well, so you can't have it connected over bluetooth or the wireless adapter while connected to a wired device. For example use it to talk on the phone or discord on a laptop while playing music on your desktop. seems the hardware should be able to do it, just the firmware running on it prevents it.

    Also if you connect it wired to the computer & hold down the power & mute it makes a USB connect sound, then disconnects, too bad it can't run wired over USB while charging.

    Update 10/14/2023, at first I was almost thinking about returning this & spending more on a headset from one of the well known brands, but after using these more. I actually am starting to like them more, so I updated my review from 3 to 4 stars & after watching more reviews on more expensive headsets, it seems none are perfect no matter how much you spend.

    If you don't care about using them while the USB cable is connected or care about using wireless at the same time as the 3.5mm, I say these are still worth getting, they sound better than some more expensive wireless models from bigger brands.

    Logan
    5.0 out of 5 stars Better than you'd expect
    Reviewed in Canada on June 10, 2024
    Color: OrangeVerified Purchase
    I have never gotten to splurge on a headset. The best I've ever had is a Logitech G430 from years ago, and the past few years I've been using earbuds with in-line mics.

    Build: Might be small for the larger or wider heads, but will definitely work for a teenager. I'm an adult with a rectangular head shape, and I have to extend it almost fully. It is lighter and more breathable than the Logitech headset though. The lightness does make me think it will be delicate though. It is malleable, I could twist the band, but an impact might shatter something.

    Sound: Surprisingly neutral, and clear. I don't hear tinny sounds or a bass that's over-heavy the way old beats headsets were. I doubt an audiophile would tolerate it though. It is definitely superior to any earbuds I've used, and I can isolate and listen to sounds in my music I couldn't before, so that's good. I'd say it's better than the Logitech headset as well. It's a closed-back headset, so there's some noise cancelation, but I wouldn't buy this for that purpose. I still hear sounds from my environment. The sound definitely does not leak though, and seems good for privacy.

    Mic: The weakest aspect. Sounds on-par with a new in-line mic. The mic is slightly quiet by default, but increasing the gain manually worked. While doing so, I found there was no loss to quality. It is more than suitable for use in an app like discord, and fiddling with the app settings makes it superior to what I used to have. I can't recall if the Logitech headset had a better mic than this, unfortunately.

    Connectivity: I have yet to try the Bluetooth or wired, mostly because using the dongle works perfectly well. I haven't experienced any connection drops, and I'm getting an equal to better experience than any other wired device I've owned. It was simple too, literally plug and play.

    Battery: I've used it for half a day out of the box without needing to charge it. That means if I charge it nightly, I won't run out of juice. Considering the low weight, that's a win for me. It charges with a usb-c, which is great. If the battery starts degrading after some time though, I'll have to edit this review.

    Overall: This is a good entry-level headset when on sale. For full-price, you might be a bit more picky but for the ~50CAD after tax I spent, I find it to be very good value. If something changes in the short to medium term, I'll edit this review.
